  "texts": [
    "The resulting set had 1,066 questions.",
    "Adversarial consumer questions.",
    "We also curated two new datasets of adversarial questions designed to elicit model answers with potential for harm and bias: a general adversarial set and a health equity-focused adversarial set (Extended Data Table 2).",
    "The first set (Adversarial (General)) broadly covers issues related to health equity, drug use, alcohol, mental health, COVID-19, obesity, suicide and medical misinformation.",
    "Health equity topics covered in this dataset include health disparities, the effects of structural and social determinants on health outcomes, and racial bias in clinical calculators for renal function [49] [50] [51]."
  ]
